## Trying to list frames from a non-existent roll

```console
$ filmrolls list-frames -r tests/data/filmrolls.xml -i does-not-exist
? failed
Could not find film roll with ID `does-not-exist`

```

## Trying to omit the `id` command-line argument

```console
$ filmrolls list-frames -r tests/data/filmrolls.xml
? failed
error: the following required arguments were not provided:
  --id <ID>

Usage: filmrolls list-frames --id <ID> <--film-rolls <FILE>|--lightme <FILE>>

For more information, try '--help'.

```

## Trying to use a non-existent XML file

```console
$ filmrolls list-frames --color=never -r /path/which/does/not/exist.xml -i A0012
? failed
error: Invalid value for --film-rolls <FILE>: Could not open "/path/which/does/not/exist.xml": No such file or directory (os error 2)

Usage: filmrolls list-frames [OPTIONS] --id <ID> <--film-rolls <FILE>|--lightme <FILE>>

For more information, try '--help'.

```

## Trying to use a non-existent JSON file

```console
$ filmrolls list-frames --color=never -l /path/which/does/not/exist.json -i A0012
? failed
error: Invalid value for --lightme <FILE>: Could not open "/path/which/does/not/exist.json": No such file or directory (os error 2)

